title: Tua Tagovailoa named Dolphins starting QB, NFL Contenders/Pretenders (Football 10/20)
description:
Surprise! The Dolphins have a new starting quarterback. Despite leading Miami to a respectable 3-3 start, Ryan Fitzpatrick has been replaced in favor of the 5th overall pick in the 2020 NFL Draft, Tua Tagovailoa. On this episode, Will Brinson is joined by Brady Quinn to break down the move (1:30). Why did the organization make this decision heading into their bye week? Can the Dolphins compete for the postseason with Tua at QB? The guys also discuss contenders and pretenders across the NFL, first focusing on AFC teams (16:30) followed by NFC teams (32:45). Should we believe in the Bills and Bears? Can the Titans and Steelers stack up with the Chiefs and Ravens? Who is for real in the NFC West? Listen to the Brady Quinn Football Show to find out.
'Pick Six' is available on Apple Podcasts, Spotify, Stitcher, Google Podcasts, Castbox and wherever else you listen to podcasts.
